.nh
.TH "BEEHIIV-SUBSCRIPTIONS-GET" "1" "Apr 2026" "beehiiv-cli" "Beehiiv CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
beehiiv-subscriptions-get - Show a subscription by ID


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbeehiiv subscriptions get  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Get subscription by ID

.PP
In previous versions of the API, another endpoint existed to retrieve a subscription by the subscriber ID. This endpoint is now deprecated and will be removed in a future version of the API. Please use this endpoint instead. The subscription ID can be found by exporting a list of subscriptions either via the \fBSettings > Publications > Export Data\fR or by exporting a CSV in a segment. Retrieve a single subscription belonging to a specific publication.

.PP
API path: /publications/{publicationId}/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for get

.PP
\fB--query\fP=[]
	Add a repeatable query parameter in key=value form


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-key\fP=""
	Override the Beehiiv API key

.PP
\fB--base-url\fP=""
	Override the API base URL

.PP
\fB--compact\fP[=false]
	Print compact JSON

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	Override the settings file location

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Print request URLs to stderr

.PP
\fB--output\fP=""
	Choose the output format (json, table, raw)

.PP
\fB--publication-id\fP=""
	Override the Beehiiv publication ID

.PP
